cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with information theory and machine learning concepts such as redundancy, synergy, and decision theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper also discusses machine learning concepts, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's application to neuroscience suggests it could belong to cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
